Bashir Mohammed, a member of the Taraba State House of Assembly, representing Nguroje State Constituency, who was kidnapped by gunmen on Wednesday, has regained freedom, a report by The PUNCH has shown. An aide to the lawmaker told The PUNCH that his boss was released by his abductors last night. Though the aide, who preferred anonymity, declined comment on how much was paid for his principal’s release, another source said millions of naira was given to the kidnappers before Mohammed was released. Our correspondent could not independently verify the specific amount of the ransom as the police and other family members decline to speak on the amount. Mohammed was said to have been rushed to an undisclosed hospital for medical attention immediately after he was reunited with his family. Police Public Relations Officer in the state, DSP David Misal, confirmed the development and said investigation was on to track down the kidnappers.  The elder brother of Governor Bala Mohammed of Bauchi State, Alhaji Adamu Mohammed Duguri, has recounted his ordeals in the hands of kidnappers. He declared that N50 million ransom was paid to secure his release. Duguri, who regained freedom after spending 13 days in kidnappers’ den, said security agents had… April 22, 2020 In "News" The Chairman of Nigeria Labour Congress, Delta State, Comrade Goodluck Ofobruku who was abducted has regained his freedom after paying an undisclosed amount of money. The Labour leader who was abducted around 8pm on Saturday while driving out of his house behind Immigration office along Ibusa/Asaba road, Asaba, the Delta… July 7, 2020 In "News" Ilorin  -  Abductors of the Chairman of the APC in Kwara, Hon. Ishola Balogun-Fulani and Secretary, Chief Bode Adekanye, have demanded for N50 million ransom. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) learnt that the kidnappers made the demand on Friday night after they had allowed the APC chiefs to speak… May 21, 2016 In "Top Stories"